HEADWORD: Electro-physiology
<hw>E*lec`tro-phys`i*ol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>That branch of physiology which treats of
electric phenomena produced through physiological agencies; it is
especially concerned with electrical impulses generated by and conducted
between nerves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

